###Base and height of smaller pyramid

The height of the smaller pyramid is $\dfrac12 \cdot 30=15\text{ cm}$.


[[☃ image 1]]

We can solve for the length $\goldE{\ell}$ in the smaller pyramid using a proportional equation.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{\goldE{\ell}}{30} &= \dfrac{15}{30}
\\\\
\goldE{\ell} &= \goldE{15}
\end{align}$

###Base and height of smaller pyramid

The height of the smaller pyramid is $10-2=8\text{ cm}$.


[[☃ image 1]]

We can solve for the length $\blueE{\ell}$ in the smaller pyramid using a proportional equation.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{\blueE{\ell}}{10} &= \dfrac{8}{10}
\\\\
\blueE{\ell} &= \blueE{8}
\end{align}$

###Greenhouse volume

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{volume}_{\text{greenhouse}}} &= \maroonD{\text{volume}_{\text{bottom}}} + \goldE{\text{volume}_{\text{top}}} \\\\
&= \maroonD{54} + \goldE{10.125\pi} \\\\
&\approx \blueE{85.8}
\end{align}$

###Volume of building

$\begin{align}
\blueE{\text{volume}_{\text{building}}} &= \maroonD{\text{volume}_{\text{entire pyramid}}} - \goldE{\text{volume}_{\text{cut off}}} \\\\
&= \maroonD{65{,}536} - \goldE{1{,}024} \\\\
&\approx \blueE{64{,}512}
\end{align}$

